# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# hermes-companion — environment variables
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your keys. The server loads `.env` at
# startup. Anything already set in your shell environment wins over `.env`.
#
# Identity, team, and the external agent command live in `config.yaml`
# (copy from config.yaml.example). This file is for secrets and runtime knobs.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── OpenAI (required) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used by the Realtime API (voice + vision). Text chat does NOT use OpenAI —
# it's a direct passthrough to the external agent configured in config.yaml.
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# ── Realtime tuning ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Model used over the Realtime WebSocket. Default: gpt-realtime-2
# REALTIME_MODEL=gpt-realtime-2

# Voice ID for spoken responses. Default: marin
# REALTIME_VOICE=marin

# Server-side VAD tuning. Defaults match the OpenAI recommended values.
# VAD_THRESHOLD=0.5
# VAD_SILENCE_MS=500
# VAD_PREFIX_PADDING_MS=300

# ── Local playback (server speakers) ────────────────────────────────────────
# Path to aplay (ALSA) for the "SPEAKERS" playback mode. Linux only.
# APLAY_BIN=/usr/bin/aplay
# LOCAL_TAIL_SAFETY_S=1.0
# LOCAL_TAIL_MAX_S=30.0

# ── Vision (optional) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Distance threshold for matching a detected face to an enrolled person.
# Lower = stricter (fewer matches). face_recognition default is 0.6.
# FACE_MATCH_THRESHOLD=0.6

# ── HTTPS (optional) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Microphone access requires HTTPS in browsers (except on localhost).
# Drop a cert pair into ./certs/ (any *.crt + matching *.key) and start.sh
# will pick them up automatically. Or set explicit paths here:
# COMPANION_CERT=/path/to/cert.crt
# COMPANION_KEY=/path/to/cert.key
